BT 0.4 g /F3 12 Tf 225.36 700 Td ([TIGRINYA: Ehnta Eyu Fidel?]) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 14 Tf 72 650 Td (The Tigrinya alphabet is called FIDEL.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 14 Tf 72 620 Td (It is one of the oldest writing systems in the world!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 14 Tf 72 590 Td (Fidel is also called the Ge'ez script.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 14 Tf 72 560 Td (Each character represents a consonant + vowel sound.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 14 Tf 72 530 Td (There are 7 forms for each base consonant.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 490 Td (In this book, we will learn the FIRST form of each letter.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 13 Tf 72 460 Td (This is called the 'Ge'ez' or first order.) Tj ET
